**edit** to add: A reason that we might want this is that it lets you have a `commentable` that is not a `post`, for instance. Theres no fixed hierarchy.

High-level question: why is this hierarchical? You could instead write:

```js
for (const x of view.repos()) this.addRepo(x);
for (const x of view.issues()) this.addIssue(x);
for (const x of view.pulls()) this.addPull(x);
for (const x of view.reviews()) this.addReview(x);
for (const x of view.comments()) this.addComment(x);
